-- Iran Guards Plan War Games in Central Region, Tehran Times Says
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 2012-02-19T06:22:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-19/iran-guards-plan-war-games-in-central-region-tehran-times-says.html
The Iranian Revolutionary Guard
Corps. ground forces will start a new round of war games in the
central Yazd province today, the  Tehran Times  newspaper
reported, citing Brigadier General Mohammad Pakpour.  The exercise is aimed at displaying the Guardsâ€™
capabilities to repel possible military offensives, increase
deterrence ability and test military equipment, Pakpour said,
according to the newspaper.  The exercises would be the third held by the Guards in the
current Iranian year, which started on March 21, 2011, the
newspaper said. The Guards held one earlier this month in
southern  Iran  and another in January in the eastern region, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
